gborough, Lincolnshire, England":"Stallingborough, Lincolnshire, England","Coswick, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom",", Somme, Co. of Vermandois, France":"Somme, Cher, Centre, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Joan FitzEustace was born about 1287, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Thomas FitzEustace, was 38 and her mother, Amice de Grey, was 34. She married Sir Robert Darcy about 1311. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1359, in Somme, Cher, Centre, France, at the age of 73."},"et":{"about 1287–1359":"umbes 1287–1359","1287–1359":"1287–1359","1270–1343":"1270–1343","1313–1383":"1313–1383","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1255–1317":"1255–1317","Abt 1313":"umbes 1313","1383":"1383","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1359":"1359","1313":"1313","after 1317":"pärast 1317","1343":"1343","1255":"1255","1287":"1287","about 1311":"umbes 1311","about 1287":"umbes 1287","1317":"1317","Hawstead, Suffolk, England":"Hawstead, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stallingborough, Lincolnshire, England":"Stallingborough, Lincolnshire, England","Coswick, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Somme, Co. of Vermandois, France":"Somme, Cher, Centre, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1287–1359":"noin 1287–1359","1287–1359":"1287–1359","1270–1343":"1270–1343","1313–1383":"1313–1383","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1255–1317":"1255–1317","Abt 1313":"noin 1313","1383":"1383","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1359":"1359","1313":"1313","after 1317":"1317 jälkeen","1343":"1343","1255":"1255","1287":"1287","about 1311":"noin 1311","about 1287":"noin 1287","1317":"1317","Hawstead, Suffolk, England":"Hawstead, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stallingborough, Lincolnshire, England":"Stallingborough, Lincolnshire, England","Coswick, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", Somme, Co. of Vermandois, France":"Somme, Cher, Centre, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1287–1359":"environ 1287–1359","1287–1359":"1287–1359","1270–1343":"1270–1343","1313–1383":"1313–1383","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1255–1317":"1255–1317","Abt 1313":"environ 1313","1383":"1383","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1359":"1359","1313":"1313","after 1317":"après 1317","1343":"1343","1255":"1255","1287":"1287","about 1311":"environ 1311","about 1287":"environ 1287",